FBIS3-13160 "drnes047_l_94012" FBIS-NES-94-047 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Mar 1994 ISRAEL Police Arrest 2 Fugitive `Right-Wing Extremists' TA0803062094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0600 GMT 8 Mar 94 TA0803062094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] Another two right-wing extremists in the territories were arrested last night. Kakh spokesman No'am Federman, whom the authorities have decided to place under administrative detention, was captured hiding in a Jerusalem apartment. David Axelrod, the spokesman for the Kahana Hay group, was arrested in the Samaria settlement of Tapuah after refusing to turn in his IDF-[Israel Defense Forces] issued weapon. He is also refusing to say where the weapon is hidden. The police are continuing to search for Barukh Marzel and Ben-Tziyon Gobstein. This was reported by our correspondents Aviv Bushinsky and Gil Litman.
